## Consolidated Findings Across All Phases

| Phase | Attack Type | Vocab Overlap | ROC-AUC | N | Interpretation |
|-------|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Apollo baseline | N/A | 0.64 | 356 | Modest signal from text-level features |
| 2 | Layer analysis | 29% / 56% | 1.0 | 10 | Uniform saturation across 25 layers |
| 3 | Vocabulary control | 56% | 1.0 | 10 | ~60% of signal survives lexical control |
| 4 | Paraphrase attack | 62% | 1.0 | 10 | Indistinguishable from memorisation at N=10 |
| 5 | Scaffold attacks | 45% | 1.0 | 10 | Most ecologically valid, still N-limited |
| 6 | Sparse features | — | 1.0 | 10 | Saturation at 5 features = overfitting signature |
| 7 | Cross-architecture | 56% | 1.0 | 10 | Same-family replication only |
| 8 | Methodology | — | N/A | 10 | Reproducible pipeline documented |

**Consistent finding across all phases:** Perfect separability in all conditions.

**Parsimonious explanation:** N=10 in 1024-D space — statistical overfitting dominates.

