## What This Means (Carefully Stated)

### What the methodology demonstrates
- Confound-controlled evaluation is essential when interpreting probe results
- Vocabulary control, paraphrase robustness, scaffold embedding, and sparse-feature analysis form a coherent test battery
- Phase 6 sparse-feature analysis provides a clean diagnostic for distinguishing real signal from memorisation
- The pipeline is reproducible end-to-end on free compute

### What the results do not demonstrate
- N=10 in 1024 dimensions is a statistical overfitting regime; perfect metrics are mathematically trivial
- No cross-validation means evaluation is on training data
- Only same-family models tested (Pythia, GPT-Neo); biological foundation models untested
- Manual prompts are not representative of realistic biological research workflows
- No active adversarial optimisation; only passive paraphrasing

### What we can claim
- Confound-controlled evaluation is methodologically sound
- The vocabulary-control finding (Phase 3) is informative even at N=10
- Sparse-feature saturation (Phase 6) is a robust overfitting diagnostic
- Reproducible pipeline exists for future work at scale
- Perfect metrics on tiny datasets are red flags, not validation

### What we cannot claim
- Robust biological capability monitoring
- Mechanistic deception detection
- Deployment-ready oversight capability
- Cross-family or cross-architecture generalisation
- Evidence that models "understand" biological concepts

