## Key Takeaway

Careful exploratory work on constrained datasets can produce methodologically sound findings even when statistical power is limited. The appropriate response to perfect metrics at N=10 is not to claim signal but to:

1. Document limitations clearly
2. Enable verification through full reproducibility
3. Identify which findings would survive proper evaluation (Phase 3 vocabulary control is the leading candidate)
4. Specify the validation roadmap (N≥100 with k-fold CV) and execute it

This is the standard progression from exploratory to validated interpretability research.

